WEBVTT

00:08.217 --> 00:09.968
[Sam] <i>It's Sam. Leave a message.</i>

00:10.052 --> 00:11.094
[line beeps]

00:11.178 --> 00:14.097
[line ringing]

00:15.599 --> 00:17.518
<i>It's Sam. Leave a message.</i>

00:17.601 --> 00:18.477
[line beeps]

00:18.560 --> 00:20.437
And then we hit 'em with the,

00:20.521 --> 00:23.106
"What about your oppressive cops,
bitches?"

00:23.190 --> 00:25.192
Except without the misogyny, right?

00:25.275 --> 00:26.944
You know, I really want to get at you,

00:27.027 --> 00:28.820
but I'm not sure how to do it
in a respectful way,

00:28.904 --> 00:30.322
random hot feminist.

00:30.405 --> 00:31.865
Guys, where's Sam?

00:31.949 --> 00:35.077
They're probably... on their way.

00:35.160 --> 00:36.370
We should just head in.

00:36.453 --> 00:37.538
It's now or never.

00:43.168 --> 00:45.671
-[dialing]
-[line ringing]

00:45.754 --> 00:47.673
[narrator]
<i>Gabe Mitchell didn't always love</i>

00:47.756 --> 00:52.177
<i>being a white face in a mostly black part</i>
<i>of an overwhelmingly white place.</i>

00:52.261 --> 00:53.804
What's up, hipster <i>8 Mile?</i>

00:53.887 --> 00:57.015
[narrator] <i>He knew jokes about his race</i>
<i>were essentially harmless.</i>

00:57.099 --> 00:58.475
All right, when I was
a community organizer--

00:58.559 --> 01:00.561
Ooh, check you out, Disney Channel Obama.

01:00.644 --> 01:02.187
What did you organize?

01:02.271 --> 01:03.730
[narrator] <i>He checked his privilege</i>

01:03.814 --> 01:05.524
<i>and supported people of color.</i>

01:05.607 --> 01:07.568
You know, I could come with.

01:07.651 --> 01:11.488
No, it's cool. It's... it's members only.

01:11.572 --> 01:13.073
[narrator]
<i>He would never presume his voice</i>

01:13.156 --> 01:15.158
<i>was more important</i>
<i>than those around him...</i>

01:15.242 --> 01:17.786
I can't believe Chad
got that travel grant over me.

01:17.869 --> 01:19.871
It's bullshit! I killed that essay.

01:19.955 --> 01:21.999
It wouldn't be America
if mediocre white men

01:22.082 --> 01:24.584
weren't being rewarded
over deserving women of color.

01:24.668 --> 01:26.295
-[narrator] <i>But...</i>
-[Sam] I'm sorry, Jo.

01:26.378 --> 01:29.798
...<i>there was a tiny part of Gabe</i>
<i>that wanted to scream.</i>

01:29.881 --> 01:31.091
You know what?

01:31.174 --> 01:33.844
Sometimes people get what they have
because they earned it.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.304
Just because I happen to be a white male

01:35.387 --> 01:37.347
does not automatically mean
I'm some asshole!

01:37.431 --> 01:38.682
Fucking white people.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.559
[all laugh]

01:40.642 --> 01:43.979
[narrator] <i>Gabe didn't always love</i>
<i>having to dodge the land mines</i>

01:44.062 --> 01:46.231
<i>of identity politics.</i>

01:46.315 --> 01:47.524
<i>However...</i>

01:50.235 --> 01:53.322
<i>Gabe loved after hours</i>
<i>at the radio station,</i>

01:53.405 --> 01:56.116
<i>debating who made the best soul records</i>

01:56.199 --> 01:58.535
<i>and, of course,</i>
<i>the great movies of all time.</i>

01:58.619 --> 02:01.747
<i>In fact, when these</i>
<i>two film majors got together,</i>

02:01.830 --> 02:03.874
<i>life was a Godard film in color,</i>

02:03.957 --> 02:06.752
<i>and the only thing that Gabe</i>
<i>loved more than Godard...</i>

02:06.835 --> 02:08.378
[line ringing]

02:08.462 --> 02:10.047
...<i>was Sam.</i>

02:11.882 --> 02:13.467
[jazz music playing]

02:13.550 --> 02:14.801
<i>♪ Waitin' by the phone ♪</i>

02:14.885 --> 02:16.678
[knocking on door]

02:17.971 --> 02:19.723
OMG.

02:19.806 --> 02:21.058
Is it <i>the </i>Samantha White?

02:21.141 --> 02:22.893
I know. I know.

02:22.976 --> 02:24.269
[sighs]

02:24.853 --> 02:25.979
Should have been there.

02:26.772 --> 02:29.608
I'm just dropping by to check your pulse,
make sure you didn't die.

02:29.691 --> 02:30.901
[grunts]

02:31.902 --> 02:33.111
Is that ice cream?

02:33.945 --> 02:36.448
Yeah, it's vanilla.
Your favorite, which is ironic.

02:38.575 --> 02:41.745
So what happened?
We missed you at the rally.

02:43.205 --> 02:45.374
Reggie... he was a mess,

02:45.457 --> 02:48.168
and it just took longer than I thought.

02:48.251 --> 02:50.253
-How did it go?
-Oh, not great.

02:50.337 --> 02:51.838
Apparently you need tickets to get in,

02:51.922 --> 02:53.590
and then Al yelled angry monologues

02:53.674 --> 02:56.385
from <i>Training Day </i>from the hallway
until we got kicked out.

02:56.468 --> 02:58.553
-I'm sorry. I should have been there.
-No, it's okay.

02:59.221 --> 03:00.639
The school's lacking in pep.

03:00.722 --> 03:02.933
There's bound to be more rallies.

03:05.268 --> 03:06.603
[sighs]

03:11.274 --> 03:12.901
[rubs hands together quickly]

03:14.653 --> 03:16.488
[chuckles]

03:21.243 --> 03:24.538
You know, it's just--
it's been such a long night,

03:24.621 --> 03:26.706
and I'm really rundown.

03:26.790 --> 03:29.209
-So I'm gonna take a shower.
-Okay.

03:31.294 --> 03:32.963
I won't be long.

03:33.046 --> 03:34.673
I'll be here.

03:38.719 --> 03:41.096
Hey, Reggie, I know you're
going through a lot right now,

03:41.179 --> 03:43.140
but whatever you need,
Sam and I are here for you.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.558
[Reggie] Thanks, I actually,

03:44.641 --> 03:46.768
think I got what I needed.

03:47.811 --> 03:49.354
Good.

03:49.438 --> 03:50.731
Super cool.

03:50.814 --> 03:53.150
Well, you know, our offer still stands.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.568
Thanks.

03:54.651 --> 03:57.237
Okay. Okay, let's start. [claps hands]

03:59.072 --> 04:00.449
[Troy] Yes, let us start, everyone.

04:00.532 --> 04:01.575
Start this meeting.

04:01.658 --> 04:02.826
Thanks for being here.

04:13.754 --> 04:14.880
[giggles]

04:18.467 --> 04:20.177
[Sam] So I know last night's rally

04:20.260 --> 04:22.137
didn't go quite as planned,

04:22.220 --> 04:24.431
but with Reggie back in the fold,

04:24.514 --> 04:27.350
I think we can all agree
that something needs to be done.

04:27.434 --> 04:29.019
Things need to change.

04:29.102 --> 04:30.896
No guns for those rent-a-cops,

04:30.979 --> 04:33.899
and fire the asshole
who went off on Reggie.

04:33.982 --> 04:35.734
[Troy] Both CORE
and the student government

04:35.817 --> 04:36.735
totally agree with you, Sam,

04:36.818 --> 04:38.904
which is why we,
along with the administration,

04:38.987 --> 04:40.363
have put together a town hall.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.115
-[clamoring]
-Fuck the town hall, man.

04:42.199 --> 04:43.867
-Yes.
-Right idea.

04:43.950 --> 04:46.953
[Troy] A town hall on the 22nd
to facilitate an open dialogue

04:47.037 --> 04:49.623
on racial tensions at Winchester.

04:49.706 --> 04:51.458
Do you feel the strings,

04:51.541 --> 04:53.877
or do they trick you
into thinking you're a real boy?

04:53.960 --> 04:56.046
[Rashid laughs] <i>Pinocchio!</i>

04:56.129 --> 04:58.131
That was my favorite movie growing up.

04:58.215 --> 05:00.592
What was the Kenyan version?
[clicking tongue]

05:00.675 --> 05:01.510
No, it was called

05:01.593 --> 05:04.095
<i>My Ancestors Were Smart Enough</i>
<i>Not to Get Captured.</i>

05:04.179 --> 05:06.932
Sam, this is what someone
who's trying to help looks like.

05:07.015 --> 05:07.849
[Gabe] Help?

05:07.933 --> 05:10.143
The administration wants a town hall
just so they can pat themselves

05:10.227 --> 05:11.812
on the back for having a town hall.

05:11.895 --> 05:13.647
We all know nothing's gonna change.

05:13.730 --> 05:16.817
-Wait. I have an--
-Don't say it.

05:16.900 --> 05:18.193
Sorry, have to.

05:18.276 --> 05:20.070
We need to protest at the town hall.

05:20.153 --> 05:21.404
Oh, I wanted to say it.

05:21.488 --> 05:23.240
You were right last night.

05:24.825 --> 05:27.327
<i>♪ Rubbing ice all over their bodies ♪</i>

05:27.410 --> 05:29.871
[Sam] Thank God for the left nipple.

05:31.581 --> 05:34.417
Thank God for the right nipple.

05:34.501 --> 05:37.379
Thank God for the abs.

05:41.174 --> 05:44.344
<i>♪ Oh, rubbing on a nipple ♪</i>

05:44.427 --> 05:46.096
[Reggie] Our pain is why we're out
in these streets.

05:46.179 --> 05:50.267
Exactly, and I'm not talking
a regular protest.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.352
We need to shut shit down.

05:52.435 --> 05:54.980
Well, maybe the system
doesn't work because you refuse to use it.

05:55.063 --> 05:57.357
Yeah, why do you have to make
everyone your enemy?

05:57.440 --> 06:00.193
-It's kind of her thing.
-Troy, you need me to be me.

06:00.277 --> 06:01.403
What are you talking about?

06:01.486 --> 06:03.655
The more radical she is,
the more acceptable you become.

06:03.738 --> 06:07.409
[Sam] We are going to bring together
every marginalized group on this campus

06:07.492 --> 06:09.786
and demand real justice.

06:09.869 --> 06:11.037
#FuckYes.

06:11.621 --> 06:13.874
I get the desire to protest,

06:13.957 --> 06:17.460
but the AASU supports the town hall.

06:17.544 --> 06:18.670
-This is--this is--
-The town hall?

06:18.753 --> 06:19.879
-You just--
-[dog barks]

06:19.963 --> 06:21.298
You tell 'em, Sorbet.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.674
[Rashid] I'm going back to Kenya,

06:22.757 --> 06:24.801
-and I mean it this time.
-[woman] I'm not going!

06:25.760 --> 06:27.053
We're doing this.

06:33.059 --> 06:36.396
Don't you wish to come in
and have sexual intercourse?

06:36.479 --> 06:38.315
Heavens, no.

06:38.398 --> 06:39.774
I have a boyfriend.

06:39.858 --> 06:41.818
I must go to him now.

06:41.902 --> 06:44.237
Yes, you should.

06:45.113 --> 06:47.699
On the other hand,

06:47.782 --> 06:51.077
sexual intercourse does sound good.

06:51.703 --> 06:54.247
[chattering]

06:54.331 --> 06:56.041
[Reggie] Now that Troy
and his sycophants are gone,

06:56.124 --> 06:57.292
we can get to work.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.628
All right, so we should probably split
into groups.

06:59.711 --> 07:00.629
[Sam] Oh, yeah.

07:00.712 --> 07:02.464
Rashid and...

07:02.547 --> 07:03.673
-Ikumi.
-Yes.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.383
-Yeah.
-Good idea, Reg.

07:05.467 --> 07:07.344
[Sam] We're gonna put you two on signs.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.137
May my art be your weapon.

07:09.220 --> 07:10.263
I'm in. I'm excited.

07:10.347 --> 07:13.475
I cannot do bubble letters,
though, just FYI.

07:13.558 --> 07:14.893
Al, we're gonna need you

07:14.976 --> 07:17.270
and the Black AF
to take the lead on social media.

07:17.354 --> 07:21.650
Also, we're gonna need water,
bullhorns, snacks,

07:21.733 --> 07:24.653
and if you get anything gluten-free,
I will smother you in your sleep.

07:24.736 --> 07:27.030
On it and completely turned on.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.658
[Sam] Reggie and I
will handle prep and permits.

07:29.741 --> 07:31.368
We've done it before.

07:31.451 --> 07:32.744
And...

07:32.827 --> 07:34.829
Oh! Joelle and Gabe,

07:34.913 --> 07:38.500
you two can canvass all
the affinity groups on campus,

07:38.583 --> 07:40.669
'cause we need to show a united front.

07:40.752 --> 07:41.920
Great.

07:42.003 --> 07:43.880
-Great.
-Looking forward to it.

07:43.964 --> 07:48.051
[Gabe] Okay, so do Sam and Reggie
hang out on, like, a daily basis?

07:48.134 --> 07:51.012
[Joelle] Gabe, you do know I don't know
where Sam is every hour of the day.

07:51.096 --> 07:53.056
Like, I'm not worried
about Reggie and Sam.

07:53.139 --> 07:55.850
Like, maybe for a second there,
but not really.

07:55.934 --> 07:57.352
I mean, I scoff at being worried.

07:57.435 --> 07:59.229
Scoff.

07:59.312 --> 08:01.189
Actually, I don't even think
I know how to scoff.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.650
I'm pretty sure it's not saying
the word "scoff," though, right?

08:03.733 --> 08:05.360
Am I talking a lot?
I feel like I'm talking a lot.

08:05.443 --> 08:08.780
No, you don't seem worried or weird
or like you're losing your mind.

08:08.863 --> 08:09.948
-[scoffs]
-[sighs]

08:10.031 --> 08:11.366
I'm not this guy, though.

08:11.449 --> 08:12.993
I'm sure everything's fine.

08:14.411 --> 08:15.912
Wait. Why'd you look at me like that?

08:15.996 --> 08:17.247
Like what? I just looked at you.

08:17.330 --> 08:21.001
No, no, no, that was a "This white boy
can't handle what I'm about to say" look.

08:21.084 --> 08:23.378
It's true. That was the look.

08:23.461 --> 08:26.715
Let's just say,
if I were you and Sam was...

08:26.798 --> 08:28.967
Never mind. Probably don't know
what I'm talking about.

08:29.050 --> 08:30.385
No, no, you can't stop there.

08:30.468 --> 08:32.012
If Sam was what?

08:32.095 --> 08:34.264
The Asian Student Alliance would love
to come out.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.016
We have a screening
of <i>Bowling for Columbine </i>that night,

08:36.099 --> 08:37.517
-but we can definitely move it.
-Oh, thank you.

08:37.600 --> 08:38.852
That's fantastic. We really appreciate it.

08:38.935 --> 08:41.229
Wait. What does <i>Bowling for Columbine</i>
have to do with being Asian?

08:41.312 --> 08:44.149
What? Just 'cause we're Asian,
we can't care about gun violence?

08:44.232 --> 08:45.942
We can only get together
and watch <i>Rashomon</i>

08:46.026 --> 08:49.029
and have conversations
about the need for sword control?

08:50.905 --> 08:52.240
Annie needs to calm the fuck down.

08:52.323 --> 08:55.160
Well, at least she's still backing us
after you low-key hate-crimed her.

08:55.243 --> 08:56.828
-[clicks tongue]
-[chuckles] Did I?

08:56.911 --> 08:58.788
-No.
-Oh.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.125
Hey, remember what you were
saying earlier before

09:02.208 --> 09:03.334
about if you were me...

09:03.460 --> 09:05.086
Fine, I just meant,

09:05.170 --> 09:06.963
if I felt like my relationship
was slipping away--

09:07.047 --> 09:08.840
Wait. Who said slipping away?

09:08.923 --> 09:11.426
If I were you,
I'd fight for my relationship.

09:12.218 --> 09:15.889
Of course, that would require me
to <i>have </i>a relationship.

09:15.972 --> 09:17.932
Young Democrats agree
that there's a problem,

09:18.016 --> 09:20.685
but we already committed
to participating in the town hall.

09:21.686 --> 09:22.896
But I wish we hadn't.

09:22.979 --> 09:24.773
I'd have my group follow you anywhere.

09:24.856 --> 09:26.691
-Nope.
-"Nope" to what?

09:26.775 --> 09:28.860
Just all of it, Mehar.

09:28.943 --> 09:30.195
Hey, what was wrong with that guy?

09:30.278 --> 09:32.030
He seemed nice. He was hot.

09:32.113 --> 09:33.239
Not my type.

09:33.323 --> 09:34.908
Well, what is your type?

09:34.991 --> 09:36.785
-Maybe I know somebody.
-You don't.

09:36.868 --> 09:38.078
Come on. Try me.

09:38.161 --> 09:40.497
[sighs] Stop following me, crazy man.

09:40.580 --> 09:43.500
The LGBTQIA Union would love to,
but we have a screening

09:43.583 --> 09:45.460
of <i>Bowling for Columbine </i>that night.

09:45.543 --> 09:47.796
Oh, we already talked to Annie,
and they're canceling that, so--

09:47.879 --> 09:49.589
[woman]
Actually, we have our own screening.

09:49.672 --> 09:51.216
But it's nice to hear
that Annie came to her senses

09:51.299 --> 09:52.425
and realized she shouldn't rip off

09:52.509 --> 09:55.011
other people's programming
just to get back at me.

09:55.095 --> 09:57.597
If you come across that bitch again,
tell her it'd be a real shame

09:57.680 --> 09:59.599
if her boyfriend found out
where she really goes

09:59.682 --> 10:01.601
when she says she's at the library.

10:01.684 --> 10:02.977
Okay, so you're busy that night.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.562
-We're gonna go.
-Motherfucker, what?

10:04.646 --> 10:06.189
I got, like, eight million questions.

10:06.272 --> 10:08.316
Girl, so-- Gabe!

10:09.317 --> 10:11.236
How <i>Defamation </i>would it be

10:11.319 --> 10:13.613
if Mehar were Annie's boyfriend?
[chuckles]

10:13.696 --> 10:15.240
Well, as long as we're on hypotheticals,

10:15.323 --> 10:16.533
who should be your boyfriend?

10:16.616 --> 10:18.368
Stop fishing for my type, Gabe.

10:18.451 --> 10:19.994
Come on, man. Bond with me.

10:20.078 --> 10:23.623
[laughs] Okay, fine.

10:23.706 --> 10:26.167
-He needs to be smart...
-Mm-hmm.

10:26.251 --> 10:29.796
...nerdy, but kind of cool,
a little bit of a badass.

10:29.879 --> 10:32.298
-Okay.
-Black.

10:32.382 --> 10:34.801
Actually, black as hell
and unapologetic about it.

10:35.927 --> 10:38.847
Kind of serious, but okay when you
make fun of him for it.

10:39.722 --> 10:42.350
Able to carry a lot on his shoulders.

10:42.433 --> 10:43.977
God, and those shoulders...

10:46.146 --> 10:47.981
You got it bad for Reggie.

10:48.064 --> 10:49.190
[gasps]

10:49.274 --> 10:50.650
Joelle.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.444
Why hasn't this happened yet?

10:53.528 --> 10:54.863
Why do you think?

10:54.946 --> 10:56.239
I have no idea.

11:12.714 --> 11:14.048
Do you think Sam and Reggie are--

11:14.132 --> 11:15.341
I don't know.

11:17.010 --> 11:18.970
I never know anything with her.

11:20.847 --> 11:21.890
As soon as I figure her out,

11:21.973 --> 11:25.226
she pulls back, and then
I-I don't know all over again.

11:27.312 --> 11:28.688
You know what I do know?

11:29.856 --> 11:31.399
-She smiles with you.
-[scoffs]

11:31.482 --> 11:33.735
Hey, that's a scoff...

11:33.818 --> 11:35.653
But I'm serious.

11:35.737 --> 11:39.782
I'm not talking a self-satisfied,
"I was dope on the radio" smile

11:39.866 --> 11:42.201
or a "pissing Troy off is fun" smile.

11:42.285 --> 11:43.912
No, with you, it's...

11:45.330 --> 11:48.041
It's a whole-body thing, head to toe.

11:49.000 --> 11:51.753
With you, she smiles from her socks.

12:03.014 --> 12:05.183
Joelle, I called the cops the other night.

12:07.310 --> 12:08.144
What?

12:08.228 --> 12:10.480
[Reggie] <i>Ooh, I'm sorry, massa.</i>

12:10.563 --> 12:12.273
[Addison] <i>It's a song.</i>
<i>Hell, it's in the title.</i>

12:12.357 --> 12:14.317
<i>-What am I supposed to do? Hum?</i>
-[Reggie] <i>Yes, nigga!</i>

12:14.400 --> 12:16.444
I thought I was protecting everybody.

12:17.445 --> 12:20.239
I thought it would keep things
from getting too out of control.

12:20.323 --> 12:22.367
I thought I was doing the right thing.

12:22.450 --> 12:25.912
I didn't-- I couldn't have known
what was gonna happen.

12:25.995 --> 12:28.206
You absolutely cannot tell Sam.

12:28.289 --> 12:29.290
But if I don't, I'm--

12:29.374 --> 12:32.377
Never mention this again,
because if she finds out...

12:35.755 --> 12:37.382
She can't find out.

12:43.346 --> 12:45.932
[Milo] I mean, I like to mix it up.

12:46.015 --> 12:47.350
[Vanessa] More Malbec, Sam?

12:47.433 --> 12:50.895
Or we can actually open
the bottle you brought.

12:51.562 --> 12:53.356
Never had wine product before.

12:54.565 --> 12:57.110
And it's a screw top. Fun.

12:57.193 --> 12:58.987
-Whatever's fine. Thanks.
-[Milo] It's so good.

12:59.070 --> 13:00.363
You guys have to listen to it.

13:00.446 --> 13:02.865
It's, like, all these great stories
of old Hollywood.

13:02.949 --> 13:05.284
<i>You Must Remember This-- </i>it's incredible.

13:05.368 --> 13:06.619
[both] "Written,

